-- Blackstone Could Invest $2 Billion in India, Economic Times Says
-- B y   U n n i   K r i s h n a n
-- 2010-09-27T01:43:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/blackstone-could-invest-another-2-billion-in-india-economic-times-says.html
Blackstone Group LP, the world’s
biggest private-equity firm, may allocate up to $2 billion for
investment in India over three years, the Economic Times
reported quoting Stephen Schwarzman, Blackstone’s chairman and
co-founder. The firm has already invested $1.2 billion since it
started operations in India five years ago, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
